# Describe the bug
Hello, 

iÂ´m using custom profiles with profile parents and in 2.4.1 profile.parent is not used as backup as expected: 

application.properties
````
my.config1=prod
my.config2=prod
%dev.my.config1=dev
%custom.quarkus.config.profile.parent=dev
%custom.my.config2=custom
````

Config.java
````
@ConfigMapping(prefix = "my")
public interface Config {
	String config1();
	String config2();
}
````

GreetingResource.java
````
@Inject
Config config;

@GET
@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN)
public String hello() {
    return String.format("config1 is %s; config2 is %s", config.config1(), config.config2());
}
````

# Expected behavior
*Output at localhost:8080 with Quarkus 2.4.0:*
config1 is dev; config2 is custom

# Actual behavior
*Output at localhost:8080 with Quarkus 2.4.1:*
config1 is prod; config2 is custom



Project is attached as zip, run with ``mvn clean compile quarkus:dev -Dquarkus.profile=custom``

[code-with-quarkus.zip](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/files/7511378/code-with-quarkus.zip)
